transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. This is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hey, how's it going?

Speaker 1: Pretty good. How about yourself?

Speaker 2: Okay, I guess. How do we cancel this stuff?

Speaker 1: I can help you out. Timothy went in Ottawa, Kansas.

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: All right. Okay, Timothy, it does look like you are a VIP member here.

Speaker 2: Do you just not need the pills as often as every single month?

Speaker 1: And need to pump the brakes for a while?

Speaker 2: What did you say again, please?

Speaker 1: Do you need to pump the brakes for a while on receiving anything?

Speaker 2: Do you just not need them every month?

Speaker 1: No, I don't need them very much.

Speaker 2: We're getting older, and the wife is not interested that much.

Speaker 1: Oh, man. I got you.

Speaker 2: If you want, what we can do is pause everything for six months at a time.

Speaker 1: That way, it doesn't come every month.

Speaker 2: It would be like once or twice a year,

Speaker 1: and then you're able to call in and request them as needed.

Speaker 2: I'll make sure this is the last one you get for a while.

Speaker 1: So what are you going to do? Say it again.

Speaker 2: I'm going to pause any future refill.

Speaker 1: We're not going to charge you or send you anything for six months at a time.

Speaker 2: Okay? It will only come once or twice a year,

Speaker 1: and then if you need them earlier,

Speaker 2: you can call in and request them as needed as well.

Speaker 1: Okay, so twice a year basically, right?

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: If she gets in the mood, I'll give you a call.

Speaker 2: Exactly. Exactly. All right.

Speaker 1: Okay. Sounds good, Timothy. I will set that up for you right now.

Speaker 2: Nothing else to worry about. Just give us a call if you need them earlier.

Speaker 1: Is there one underway now, though?

Speaker 2: Yeah. I'm going to make sure that's the last one for a while, okay?

Speaker 1: I'll take that. I'll be all right.

Speaker 2: Okay. Sounds good. All right, Timothy. Hope you have a great one.

Speaker 1: All right. Thank you very much. Bye.

Speaker 2: Take care. Bye-bye.
